Clinical implications of the ethics of informed consent for first-trimester risk assessment for trisomy 21. We identify the clinical implications of the ethics of informed consent for risk assessment for trisomy 21.Based on the ethics of informed consent, we find that routinely offering first-trimester risk assessment in centers qualified to provide it is ethically obligatory, and routinely withholding the results of first-trimester risk assessment is ethically unjustified.The ethics of informed consent is an essential dimension of first-trimester risk assessment for trisomy 21.